 R‚Üê‚çôGitMerge ‚çôRA;‚çôCMD;‚çôTEMP;‚çôWS

‚çù Merge any changes to git tracked files fetched from the remote repo
‚çù with your current code.  Inserts merge conflict indicators into files
‚çù where merges cannot be done automatically.  To resolve these, remove
‚çù the added markers from the code manually (fixing the merge) and then
‚çù once a finalized piece of code/object is ready, ]Git Add <OBJ> to
‚çù mark the merge conflict as resolved and then ]Git Commit and ]Git Push
‚çù to finalize the merge.
‚çù
‚çù [TLDR: UMerges fetched code with local code]

‚çù Syntax: R‚Üê‚çôGitMerge [PARAMS] [TEMP] [WS]
‚çù   TEMP: Temp dir for use by ‚çôCOMMAND
‚çù     WS: WS' parent dir
‚çù PARAMS: Additional modifiers for the merge command like branch names
‚çù         (e.g. ]Git Merge branch-name to merge "branch-name" into the
‚çù         current branch)

